definition: full and bulging (of a pocket, pouch etc)
drum/CL:通[tong4],面[mian4]/to drum/to strike/to rouse/to bulge/to swell
drum/CL:通[tong4],面[mian4]/to drum/to strike/to rouse/to bulge/to swell

sentences.english: Next up is the bulging pencil case.
sentences.chinese: 下一步就是鼓鼓囊囊的铅笔盒。

sentences.english: My files now bulge with more than 800 rejections.
sentences.chinese: 如今，我的文件夹被八百余封拒信塞得鼓鼓囊囊。

sentences.english: and the sight of everyone carrying bags bulging with food.
sentences.chinese: 以及人人手里大包小包拎着鼓鼓囊囊食品袋的景象。

sentences.english: She carried a filled canvas satchel.
sentences.chinese: 她带了一个鼓鼓囊囊的帆布包。

sentences.english: There was a string of tiny clouds shaped like miniature plump sausages.
sentences.chinese: 附近一抹微云形如一串鼓鼓囊囊的小香肠。

sentences.english: His pocket bulged with small stone.
sentences.chinese: 他的囗袋鼓鼓囊囊装满了小石头。

sentences.english: His schoolbag was bulging with apples when he came back from his uncle"s orchard."
sentences.chinese: 他从叔叔的果园回来时书包里鼓鼓囊囊装满了苹果。

definition: cloth pouch open in the middle, forming two bags/jacket worn for Chinese wrestling
pouch/sack/bag/Budai (the Laughing Buddha)/Budai or Putai town in Chiayi county 嘉義縣|嘉义县[Jia1 yi4 xian4], west Taiwan
